Thus, the Fe(II) ions are bridged by the mercapto sulfur atoms of the Hmna ligands, which gives rise to a new one-dimensional linear structure (Fig. 1b). The distance of the neighboring Fe(II) ions is 3.692 Å. The one-dimensional chain is parallel to a axis (Fig. 1c) and interacts with the neighboring coordination chains via intermolecular hydrogen bonds to further form a three-dimensional supramolecular construction, as shown in Fig. 2
                     . Specifically, the pyridyl nitrogen atoms serve as proton donors, while the uncoordinated carboxylate oxygen atoms act as proton acceptors. The hydrogen bond with NH⋯O distance is 2.754(2) Å (Table 3
                     ).
